Currently if the user creates a different status and transitions an issue (that is in a completed sprint) or change the project Workflow, the historical data will be affected. For example, the sprint report will show the completed issue as still incomplete.

As an Agile Administrator, I would like to change the status in my workflow and the Agile plugin recognise all these changes and adjust it in the historical data on its reports.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-11833].
  {panel}

As a user, I would like to be able search by the values in the "Epic Link" field from the _basic_ mode in the issue navigator.

At the moment, this is not supported and I am prompted to use _advanced_ search instead.

This was cloned because it had the status resolved, but still it is not possible!

h3. Expected behavior
Epic labels will keep shown on issues when re-ordering those in a board

h3. Actual behavior
Epic labels disappear in all issues anytime an issue is reordered in a board

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create some issues on an Agile-enabled project;
# Assign those issues to Epic(s);
# Start a new sprint;
# Move issues with Epic labels to the sprint;
# When on "Active Sprint" view, re-order issues;

h3. Workaround
Refresh the browser after performing changes in the board.

h4. Steps to Reproduce:
# Install JIRA 6.3.15;
# Install JIRA Agile 6.6.60;
# Create a Custom Field of type Text Field (multi-line);
# Add it to the Default Screen;
# Create a Project and a board;
# Change the Renderer of this field in this project to Wiki Markup;
# Navigate to the board and create an Epic;
# Create an issue (from anywhere inside JIRA Agile)
# Add something to the new field and change focus.

h4. Expected Behavior:
JIRA would change the focus to the next field accordingly.

h4. Actual Behavior:
JIRA shows an error as shown in the video attached ([^error.mov]). There is also a backup attached that can be used to replicate this (account/password: matheus/matheus).

This issue is also happening for Custom User Pickers (Single and Multi)
